		<h3 class="snippettitle">Selecting & moving pieces</h3>
		<p class="snippetdescription">Our chess app uses algorithms that we wrote on the Rails backend to show the player what their possible moves are, following standard chess logic. Players can drag and drop pieces with a click of a mouse.</p>
		<br>
		<h3 class="snippettitle">Real-time Updates</h3>
		<p class="snippetdescription">When a player moves or captures a piece, opponents can see these updates in real-time, due to our app's integration with Firebase's real-time database.</p>
	</div>

  <!-- SNIPPET -->
  <div class="codesnippet2 col-lg-6 col-md-6 col-xs-12">
		<h3 class="snippettitle">Moves</h3>
		<p class="snippetdescription">We log the list of moves next to the chessboard for each game, keeping track of the piece coordinates and game's turn. This log updates live and in real-time for both players.</p>
		<br><br>
		<h3 class="snippettitle">Captured pieces</h3>
		<p class="snippetdescription">
		  We also display captured pieces in real-time, separated by piece color.
		</p>
	</div>

